<TEXT>
GPT, the UK-based telecommunications manufacturing joint venture between GEC
and Siemens, has won a contract worth about Pounds 10m to supply exchanges
to Southwestern Bell for its UK cable telephone network, Andrew Adonis
writes.
The order is for up to 10 System X digital telephone exchanges. Southwestern
Bell, the regional US operator, is building networks in seven urban areas,
including Liverpool, central Lancashire, Telford and Wigan, with Cox Cable
Communications.
Southwestern Bell is the third largest cable TV and telephone operator in
the UK, behind Nynex and Telewest. Its seven franchises cover about 1.2m
homes. Most cable operators are installing their own switching equipment.
