FT  21 OCT 93 / Renovated fish market reopens
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ASSOCIATED British Ports will today officially open England's largest fresh
fish auction market after a Pounds 300,000 investment programme to bring it
up to new European Community standards, Ian Hamilton Fazey writes. The
government has met about 20 per cent of the cost.
The market - a 60,000 sq ft group of covered sheds - handles 50,000 tonnes
of fish a year. The development has given Hull an edge over Grimsby,
traditionally one of Britain's pre-eminent fishing ports, which lies across
the Humber on the south bank of the estuary.
Grimsby, which - like Hull - is owned by ABP, is having to spend more than
Pounds 8m to rebuild its fish auction sheds to meet the new standards.
