<TEXT>
THE National Lottery Bill last night completed its passage through
parliament, clearing the way for the first Pounds 1m prize draw to take
place on schedule late next year or early 1995, David Owen writes.
The bill now goes for royal assent some three months later than the
government had originally hoped. Mr Iain Sproat, national heritage minister,
told MPs that in spite of this he was still hopeful that the first draw
would take place on time.
