FT  20 OCT 93 / London Stock Exchange: Virtuality excels
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A sparkling debut from Virtuality, the specialist software producer, saw the
shares zoom to a premium of 119p over the listing price of 170p. The shares
closed at 289p with turnover reaching 5.7m, more than one third of
yesterday's placing.
Dealers said the shares, which went to around 80 institutions, moved to an
immediate subtantial premium before gathering momentum during the session.
They hit a bid high of 315p in the afternoon before coming back at the
close.
Virtuality's strong showing carries on the successful run of market debuts.
Last week, Parkdean Leisure went to a 6 per cent premium on its first day.
It closed a penny ahead yesterday at 133p, up 13 from its float price.
