FT  20 OCT 93 / International Company News: Polaroid hit by poor third term
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES in Polaroid, the US photography group, fell sharply yesterday after
it posted a 10 per cent downturn in third-quarter earnings.
For the three months to end-September, net earnings were Dollars 24.9m, or
53 cents a share, against Dollars 27. m, or 59 cents, in the corresponding
period of 1992. Profits fell in spite of a 4 per cent increase in revenues
to Dollars 533.9m.
On Wall Street, the stock closed at Dollars 32 5/8 , down Dollars 1 1/2 on
the day.
The Massachusetts-based company attributed its lacklustre performance to
currency fluctuations and the cost of launching its Captiva instant camera
system.
