<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MONSANTO, the big US chemicals company, unveiled stronger than expected
third quarter net income of Dollars 95m, or 78 cents a share, up from
Dollars 54m, or 45 cents a year earlier.
Last year's results included gains of Dollars 8m, or 6 cents, from
discontinued operations. Sales slid to Dollars 1.85bn from Dollars 1.88bn.
Monsanto said operating income from its Searle pharmaceutical subsidiary has
started to turn around thanks to sales growth from new products. Operating
income from its chemical group improved to Dollars 77m from Dollars 34m,
reflecting higher demand for nylon fibers and continuing cost reduction
measures.
