<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 93 / UK Company News: S Jerome returns to the black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COST CUTTING and increased turnover enabled S Jerome &amp; Sons (Holdings), the
West Yorkshire-based spinner and weaver, to return pre-tax profits of Pounds
25,000 for the six months to June 30, against losses of Pounds 9,000.
The company is returning to the dividend list with a 0.2p interim, its first
payment since 1991.
The comparative figure included Pounds 153,000 profits from its electronics
business sold last year. Turnover was Pounds 12.2m (Pounds 21.5m). Turnover
for continuing activities was Pounds 10.8m with pre-tax losses of Pounds
162,000.
Earnings per share came out at 0.2p (losses 0.08p).
The company said that it had received a claim from the purchase of its
electronics company but it was impossible at present to assess the extent of
any liability.
