Ridsdale resigned as joint chief operating officers.
John Sadler, a former finance director of the John Lewis Partnership was
appointed non-executive chairman and John Osborn, a former director of
Sears, took over as chief executive.
Alexon lost nearly Pounds 1m before tax last year and passed its final
dividend; it had made an Pounds 11.3m profit in the previous year. Its
interim figures showed a pre-tax loss of Pounds 10.2m, against profits of
Pounds 1.5m last time round.
