<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT last night awarded a Pounds 200m contract for ammunition to
Royal Ordnance, ending a period of uncertainty for the British Aerospace
subsidiary, David Owen writes.
The move, which was announced in the Commons debate on defence by Mr Jeremy
Hanley, the armed forces minister, will help safeguard nearly 1,000 jobs
over five years.
Royal Ordnance said it was 'delighted' at the news. On a purely commercial
basis, the contract represented 'a good deal for the government and the
taxpayer'.
