<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 93 / Orange juice goes on VAT list
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CUSTOMS &amp; EXCISE yesterday squeezed value added tax out of orange juice
sellers after conflicting results in appeals by manufacturers last year.
The 1993 Valued Added Tax (Beverages) Order, which was introduced in
parliament yesterday, extends from the end of this year standard-rate VAT to
all beverages except milk and other named exemptions.
Customs said the change would provide up to Pounds 5m in additional VAT
revenues, but stressed that it had introduced the change to introduce
consistency to the rules. Its decision followed 'representations from UK
apple juice producers' who were keen that their products, which are
VAT-rated, should be treated in the same way as similar juices.
