<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 93 / Signs of revival in executive recruiting
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EXECUTIVE recruitment is showing signs of recovery with the highest growth
for five years recorded in demand for staff, the latest quarterly survey by
MSL, the human resource consultancy, shows, Robert Taylor writes.
Overall senior recruitment rose by 15 per cent but the biggest growth in
demand has been in the high technology sector, which rose 117 per cent in
the quarter to September, followed by sales and marketing with a 73 per cent
improvement. There was a 50 per cent increase in the demand for senior
managers in retailing, 48 per cent in energy related industries, and 27 per
cent in general management.
The survey's quarterly index - which began in 1959 - is based on the
monitoring of advertised demand for executives and managers.
The trend for the first six months of the year was flat although this was an
improvement on the previous 17 months of steady decline.
