<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 93 / Sizewell C 'would give Pounds 285m boost'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BUILDING the Sizewell C nuclear power station would give a Pounds 285m boost
to the regional economy, Nuclear Electric, the state-owned generator, said
yesterday.
It has applied for permission to build a Pounds 3.5bn twin-reactor at the
Suffolk site where Britain's first pressurised water reactor plant is
nearing completion.
